<p itemprop="description">A lead data ethicist defines the strategic approach to data ethics across the organisation and industry. They shape ethical standards, influence policy development, and lead transformational initiatives to embed responsible data practices at scale.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Define strategic vision for data ethics and responsible data use across the organisation</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Influence policy development and regulatory approaches at national and international levels</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Lead transformational initiatives to embed ethical practices in organisational culture</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Build partnerships with academic institutions, industry bodies, and regulatory authorities</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Establish the organisation as a thought leader in responsible data use</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Drive innovation in ethical frameworks and assessment methodologies</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Advise executive leadership on strategic ethical considerations</li>
    </ul>
</section>

